as.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7430,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/02\/beware-firasah-believer\/","url_meta":{"origin":19883,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Firasah: Believers have insight from the light of Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 2, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa'id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace be upon him, said, \u201cBeware of the intuition\u00a0of the believer. Verily, he sees with the light of Allah.\u201d Then, the Prophet recited the verse, \u201cVerily, in that are signs for those of discernment.\u201d (15:75) Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3127 Grade: Hasan (fair)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":12535,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/27\/ibn-qayyim-jihad-never-fought\/","url_meta":{"origin":19883,"position":3},"title":"Ibn Qayyim on Jihad: The Prophet never fought peaceful people","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 27, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn al-Qayyim, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cThe Prophet never forced the religion upon anyone, but rather he only fought those who waged war against him and fought him first. As for those who made peace with him or conducted a truce, then he never fought them and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6031,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/07\/ibn-al-qayyim-deen-husn-khuluq\/","url_meta":{"origin":19883,"position":4},"title":"Ibn Qayyim on Akhlaq: Entire religion is good character, manners","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 7, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn al-Qayyim, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cThe religion itself is entirely good character, so whoever surpasses you in character has surpassed you in religion. Likewise, it is such with spirituality (al-tasawwuf). Al-Kanani said: Spirituality is itself good character, so whoever surpasses you in character has surpassed you\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21031,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/10\/13\/fatwa-hikmah-ibn-abbas\/","url_meta":{"origin":19883,"position":5},"title":"Ibn Abbas on Fatwa: Wisdom in issuing legal verdicts","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 13, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Sa\u2019d ibn 'Ubaydah reported: A man came to Ibn Abbas, may Allah be pleased with him, and he said, \u201cIs there repentance for one who kills a believer?\u201d Ibn Abbas said, \u201cNo, there is nothing but Hellfire.\u201d After the man left, those sitting nearby said to him, \u201cWhat is this?\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.